Beinn Liath Mhor Fannaich

Hear pronunciation Press to hear pronunciation

Beinn Liath Mhor Fannaich is a bulky Munro situated just to the north of the main Fannichs ridge. It offers good views both of the neighbouring and over to the Beinn Dearg range.

 You have not climbed Beinn Liath Mhor Fannaich.

Region: Ullapool

Altitude: 954 metres

Users' Rating:
  • Currently 2.88/5
Rating: 2.9/5 (51 votes cast)

You must be registered and signed-in to vote

Detailed route description and map

Sgurr Mor and the eastern Fannichs from the Dirrie Mor

Other routes and challenges

Many different combinations of summits can be done, such as including the '/ullapool/sgurrnanclachgeala.shtml'>Sgurr nan Clach Geala group for three more Munros, or even the ultimate epic challenge: the great traverse of all 9 Fannichs Munros.
